humanMachineDialogue.author: ZS Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The N stage for axillary lymph node metastasis is determined by the number of positive lymph nodes. In this report, it is mentioned that there are metastases and micrometastases in axillary lymph nodes (NHG2; pT2; pN3a). Further, the report mentions 'Metastases et micrometastases carcinomatosae in lymphonodis axillae (No XXV/XXVIII)', which means that out of 28 examined lymph nodes, 25 had cancer involvement. This places the patient in N3 stage, as N3 stage is defined as metastasis in 4 or more axillary lymph nodes or in infraclavicular (claviicular) lymph nodes.
